  "texts": [
    "Next to the roles for the new AI Office and the European Data Protection Supervisor, an Advisory forum representing multiple stakeholders including industry and civil society will be established (Article 67 AIA), as well as a scientific panel of independent experts (Article 68 AIA).",
    "Most enforcement powers -with the notable exception of the enforcement of provisions relating to requirements and obligations concerning general-purpose AI as set out in Articles 88-94 of the AIA -will remain with member states and will be coordinated at national level through designated market surveillance authorities.",
    "The enforcement structure between member states will most likely differ strongly and become quite complex overall, as it is possible to have multiple national competent authorities.",
    "Only the designation of a single point of contact is necessary (see Article 70 par.1, 2).",
    "Hence, within member states and according to their different national administrative traditions, it is possible that the governance and enforcement will be divided across several existing or newly established authorities, as long as there is a single point of contact."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}